= About Me

~~~
{}{img_left}{ProfilePic.jpeg}{WHAT}{215px}{300}{}
Anthony Ostuni 

I am a first-year PhD student in [UC San Diego https://cse.ucsd.edu/]'s [theory group https://cstheory.ucsd.edu/home.html],
where I am extremely fortuate to be advised by [Daniel Kane https://cseweb.ucsd.edu/~dakane/] and 
[Shachar Lovett http://cseweb.ucsd.edu/~slovett/home.html]. I completed my undergraduate studies at the 
[https://umd.edu/ University of Maryland] (UMD), receiving a BS in computer science and applied mathematics.

I've previously spent time as a researcher at UMD's [http://www.cs.umd.edu/projects/reucaar/ Combinatorics and 
Algorithms for Real Problems] REU program, as well as a 
software engineering intern at [https://careers.google.com/students/engineering-and-technical-internships/ Google] 
and the [https://www.jhuapl.edu/ Johns Hopkins Applied Physics Laboratory]. 
~~~

== Research Interests

My primary areas of interest are combinatorics and algorithms, specifically extremal combinatorics and 
spectral graph theory. See [papers.html Papers] for my publications.

